ENTRY            D0813   20260417   20260528   20260528       D152
SUBENT        D0813001   20260417   20260528   20260528       D152
BIB                  7         11
TITLE      Measurement of the effect of large deformation-aligned
            ground-state spin on fission fragment anisotropies
AUTHOR     (R.D.Butt, D.J.Hinde, M.Dasgupta, A.C.Berriman,
           A.Mukherjee, C.R.Morton, J.O.Newton)
INSTITUTE  (3AULCBR)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,66,044601,2002)
           #doi:10.1103/PhysRevC.66.044601
FACILITY   (VDGT,3AULCBR) 14UD tandem accelerator.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information on source of uncertainty.
HISTORY    (20160714C) VS.
           (20260417A) Entry revised
ENDBIB              11
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           14
SUBENT        D0813002   20260417   20260528   20260528       D152
BIB                  8         17
REACTION  1(72-HF-178(14-SI-28,F),,SIG)
          2((72-HF-178(14-SI-28,F),,DA)//
           (72-HF-178(14-SI-28,F),,DA))
INC-SPECT  The pulsed beam consisted of 1 ns long
           bursts separated by 106 ns.
DETECTOR   (MWPC)A large position-sensitive multiwire detector
            (357 X 284 mm) covered 95-170 degree, calibrated
            using Rutherford scattering of 31P on 197Au below the
            fusion barrier.
SAMPLE     178Hf targets consisted of 200 mg/cm2 of metal
           evaporated onto 30 mg/cm2 backing foils of aluminum.
METHOD     (TOF) Time-of-flight measurements of fission fragments
ANALYSIS   (INTAD) Fission fragment angular distributions were
            converted to the center-of-mass frame and fitted
            (zero spin) to obtain cross sections and anisotropies.
STATUS     (TABLE,,R.D.Butt+,J,PR/C,66,044601,2002) Table II
HISTORY    (20260417U) VT. STATUS updated
ENDBIB              17
COMMON               2          3
ANG-NM    2ANG-DN    2
ADEG       ADEG
       180.        90.
ENDCOMMON            3
