SUBENT        D0813003   20260417   20260528   20260528       D152
BIB                  8         15
REACTION   (72-HF-178(14-SI-28,FUS),,SIG,ER)
INC-SPECT  The beam was chopped with 1 s on 1 s off.
DETECTOR   (SIBAR) Annular silicon surface barrier detector placed
           at 174 degree used to measure the alpha decay of the
           evaporation residues stopped in a 1.9 ug/cm2 Al catcher
PART-DET   (A) Alpha decay of the residues T1/2 ranged from
               3.5 s to 11.5 min.
SAMPLE     178Hf targets consisted of 200 mg/cm2 of metal
           evaporated onto 30 mg/cm2 backing foils of aluminum.
ANALYSIS   The total evaporation residue cross section was
           determined from the measured individual evaporation
           residues cross sections.
